{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to talk about post-conflict recovery"},{"time":6000,"text":"and how we might do post-conflict recovery better."},{"time":11000,"text":"The record on post-conflict recovery is not very impressive."},{"time":16000,"text":"40 percent of all post-conflict situations,"},{"time":20000,"text":"historically, have reverted back to conflict within a decade."},{"time":24000,"text":"In fact, they've accounted for half of all civil wars."},{"time":29000,"text":"Why has the record been so poor?"},{"time":32000,"text":"Well, the conventional approach"},{"time":35000,"text":"to post-conflict situations"},{"time":37000,"text":"has rested on, on kind of, three principles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41000,"text":"The first principle is: it's the politics that matters."},{"time":46000,"text":"So, the first thing that is prioritized is politics."},{"time":49000,"text":"Try and build a political settlement first."},{"time":54000,"text":"And then the second step is to say,"},{"time":57000,"text":"\"The situation is admittedly dangerous, but only for a short time.\""},{"time":60000,"text":"So get peacekeepers there, but get them home as soon as possible."},{"time":65000,"text":"So, short-term peacekeepers."},{"time":68000,"text":"And thirdly, what is the exit strategy for the peacekeepers?"},{"time":72000,"text":"It's an election."},{"time":74000,"text":"That will produce a legitimate and accountable government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"So that's the conventional approach."},{"time":82000,"text":"I think that approach denies reality."},{"time":86000,"text":"We see that there is no quick fix."},{"time":90000,"text":"There's certainly no quick security fix."},{"time":93000,"text":"I've tried to look at the risks of reversion to conflict,"},{"time":96000,"text":"during our post-conflict decade."},{"time":98000,"text":"And the risks stay high throughout the decade."},{"time":102000,"text":"And they stay high regardless of the political innovations."},{"time":109000,"text":"Does an election produce an accountable and legitimate government?"},{"time":114000,"text":"What an election produces is a winner and a loser."},{"time":119000,"text":"And the loser is unreconciled."},{"time":124000,"text":"The reality is that we need to reverse the sequence."},{"time":128000,"text":"It's not the politics first;"},{"time":130000,"text":"it's actually the politics last."},{"time":133000,"text":"The politics become easier as the decade progresses"},{"time":136000,"text":"if you're building on a foundation"},{"time":139000,"text":"of security and economic development --"},{"time":144000,"text":"the rebuilding of prosperity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"Why does the politics get easier?"},{"time":148000,"text":"And why is it so difficult initially?"},{"time":150000,"text":"Because after years of stagnation and decline,"},{"time":154000,"text":"the mentality of politics is that it's a zero-sum game."},{"time":160000,"text":"If the reality is stagnation,"},{"time":162000,"text":"I can only go up if you go down."},{"time":165000,"text":"And that doesn't produce a productive politics."},{"time":170000,"text":"And so the mentality has to shift from"},{"time":173000,"text":"zero-sum to positive-sum"},{"time":175000,"text":"before you can get a productive politics."},{"time":179000,"text":"You can only get positive, that mental shift,"},{"time":181000,"text":"if the reality is that prosperity is being built."},{"time":185000,"text":"And in order to build prosperity, we need security in place."},{"time":190000,"text":"So that is what you get when you face reality."},{"time":192000,"text":"But the objective of facing reality"},{"time":194000,"text":"is to change reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196000,"text":"And so now let me suggest"},{"time":198000,"text":"two complimentary approaches"},{"time":202000,"text":"to changing the reality of the situations."},{"time":205000,"text":"The first is to recognize the interdependence"},{"time":209000,"text":"of three key actors, who are different actors,"},{"time":214000,"text":"and at the moment are uncoordinated."},{"time":217000,"text":"The first actor is the Security Council."},{"time":220000,"text":"The Security Council typically has the responsibility"},{"time":224000,"text":"for providing the peacekeepers"},{"time":226000,"text":"who build the security."},{"time":229000,"text":"And that needs to be recognized,"},{"time":231000,"text":"first of all, that peacekeeping works."},{"time":234000,"text":"It is a cost-effective approach."},{"time":236000,"text":"It does increase security."},{"time":239000,"text":"But it needs to be done long-term."},{"time":241000,"text":"It needs to be a decade-long approach,"},{"time":243000,"text":"rather than just a couple of years."},{"time":245000,"text":"That's one actor, the Security Council."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"The second actor, different cast of guys,"},{"time":251000,"text":"is the donors."},{"time":253000,"text":"The donors provide post-conflict aid."},{"time":256000,"text":"Typically in the past,"},{"time":259000,"text":"the donors have been interested in the first couple of years,"},{"time":262000,"text":"and then they got bored."},{"time":264000,"text":"They moved on to some other situation."},{"time":267000,"text":"Post-conflict economic recovery"},{"time":269000,"text":"is a slow process."},{"time":271000,"text":"There are no quick processes in economics"},{"time":274000,"text":"except decline."},{"time":276000,"text":"You can do that quite fast."},{"time":278000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":279000,"text":"So the donors have to stick with this situation"},{"time":284000,"text":"for at least a decade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"And then the third key actor"},{"time":290000,"text":"is the post-conflict government."},{"time":293000,"text":"And there are two key things it's got to do."},{"time":295000,"text":"One is it's got to do economic reform,"},{"time":299000,"text":"not fuss about the political constitution."},{"time":302000,"text":"It's got to reform economic policy."},{"time":304000,"text":"Why? Because during conflict"},{"time":307000,"text":"economic policy typically deteriorates."},{"time":310000,"text":"Governments snatch short-term opportunities"},{"time":314000,"text":"and, by the end of the conflict, the chickens have come home to roost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"So this legacy of conflict is really bad economic policy."},{"time":321000,"text":"So there is a reform agenda, and there is an inclusion agenda."},{"time":325000,"text":"The inclusion agenda doesn't come from elections."},{"time":328000,"text":"Elections produce a loser, who is then excluded."},{"time":333000,"text":"So the inclusion agenda means genuinely"},{"time":336000,"text":"bringing people inside the tent."},{"time":339000,"text":"So those three actors."},{"time":341000,"text":"And they are interdependent"},{"time":343000,"text":"over a long term."},{"time":346000,"text":"If the Security Council doesn't commit to security"},{"time":350000,"text":"over the course of a decade,"},{"time":352000,"text":"you don't get the reassurance which produces private investment."},{"time":356000,"text":"If you don't get the policy reform and the aid,"},{"time":360000,"text":"you don't get the economic recovery,"},{"time":362000,"text":"which is the true exit strategy for the peacekeepers."},{"time":366000,"text":"So we should recognize that interdependence,"},{"time":370000,"text":"by formal, mutual commitments."},{"time":373000,"text":"The United Nations actually has a language"},{"time":376000,"text":"for these mutual commitments, the recognition of mutual commitments;"},{"time":379000,"text":"it's called the language of compact."},{"time":383000,"text":"And so we need a post-conflict compact."},{"time":386000,"text":"The United Nations even has an agency which could broker these compacts;"},{"time":389000,"text":"it's called the Peace Building Commission."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393000,"text":"It would be ideal to have a standard set of norms"},{"time":398000,"text":"where, when we got to a post-conflict situation,"},{"time":401000,"text":"there was an expectation of these mutual commitments"},{"time":405000,"text":"from the three parties."},{"time":408000,"text":"So that's idea one:"},{"time":411000,"text":"recognize interdependence."},{"time":414000,"text":"And now let me turn to the second approach, which is complimentary."},{"time":418000,"text":"And that is to focus on a few critical objectives."},{"time":427000,"text":"Typical post-conflict situation is a zoo"},{"time":430000,"text":"of different actors with different priorities."},{"time":434000,"text":"And indeed, unfortunately, if you navigate by needs"},{"time":438000,"text":"you get a very unfocused agenda,"},{"time":441000,"text":"because in these situations, needs are everywhere,"},{"time":444000,"text":"but the capacity to implement change is very limited."},{"time":448000,"text":"So we have to be disciplined and focus on things that are critical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453000,"text":"And I want to suggest that in the typical post-conflict situation"},{"time":456000,"text":"three things are critical."},{"time":459000,"text":"One is jobs."},{"time":461000,"text":"One is improvements in basic services --"},{"time":463000,"text":"especially health, which is a disaster during conflict."},{"time":467000,"text":"So jobs, health, and clean government."},{"time":472000,"text":"Those are the three critical priorities."},{"time":476000,"text":"So I'm going to talk a little about each of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"Jobs."},{"time":480000,"text":"What is a distinctive approach"},{"time":483000,"text":"to generating jobs in post-conflict situations?"},{"time":486000,"text":"And why are jobs so important?"},{"time":488000,"text":"Jobs for whom? Especially jobs for young men."},{"time":493000,"text":"In post-conflict situations,"},{"time":495000,"text":"the reason that they so often revert to conflict,"},{"time":499000,"text":"is not because elderly women get upset."},{"time":502000,"text":"It's because young men get upset."},{"time":505000,"text":"And why are they upset? Because they have nothing to do."},{"time":508000,"text":"And so we need a process of generating jobs,"},{"time":514000,"text":"for ordinary young men, fast."},{"time":517000,"text":"Now, that is difficult."},{"time":520000,"text":"Governments in post-conflict situation"},{"time":522000,"text":"often respond by puffing up the civil service."},{"time":526000,"text":"That is not a good idea."},{"time":528000,"text":"It's not sustainable."},{"time":530000,"text":"In fact, you're building a long-term liability"},{"time":533000,"text":"by inflating civil service."},{"time":535000,"text":"But getting the private sector to expand is also difficult,"},{"time":539000,"text":"because any activity which is open to international trade"},{"time":544000,"text":"is basically going to be uncompetitive"},{"time":546000,"text":"in a post-conflict situation."},{"time":548000,"text":"These are not environments where you can build export manufacturing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553000,"text":"There's one sector which isn't exposed to international trade,"},{"time":558000,"text":"and which can generate a lot of jobs,"},{"time":561000,"text":"and which is, in any case, a sensible sector"},{"time":563000,"text":"to expand, post-conflict,"},{"time":565000,"text":"and that is the construction sector."},{"time":569000,"text":"The construction sector has a vital role,"},{"time":572000,"text":"obviously, in reconstruction."},{"time":575000,"text":"But typically that sector has withered away during conflict."},{"time":580000,"text":"During conflict people are doing destruction."},{"time":582000,"text":"There isn't any construction going on. And so the sector shrivels away."},{"time":586000,"text":"And then when you try and expand it,"},{"time":588000,"text":"because it's shriveled away,"},{"time":590000,"text":"you encounter a lot of bottlenecks."},{"time":593000,"text":"Basically, prices soar"},{"time":595000,"text":"and crooked politicians then milk the rents from the sector,"},{"time":599000,"text":"but it doesn't generate any jobs."},{"time":601000,"text":"And so the policy priority is to break the bottlenecks"},{"time":604000,"text":"in expanding the construction sector."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607000,"text":"What might the bottlenecks be?"},{"time":609000,"text":"Just think what you have to do"},{"time":612000,"text":"successfully to build a structure, using a lot of labor."},{"time":615000,"text":"First you need access to land."},{"time":617000,"text":"Often the legal system is broken down"},{"time":619000,"text":"so you can't even get access to land."},{"time":621000,"text":"Secondly you need skills,"},{"time":623000,"text":"the mundane skills of the construction sector."},{"time":627000,"text":"In post-conflict situations we don't just need Doctors Without Borders,"},{"time":631000,"text":"we need Bricklayers Without Borders,"},{"time":633000,"text":"to rebuild the skill set."},{"time":636000,"text":"We need firms. The firms have gone away."},{"time":639000,"text":"So we need to encourage the growth of local firms."},{"time":642000,"text":"If we do that, we not only get the jobs,"},{"time":645000,"text":"we get the improvements in public infrastructure,"},{"time":648000,"text":"the restoration of public infrastructure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651000,"text":"Let me turn from jobs to the second objective,"},{"time":657000,"text":"which is improving basic social services."},{"time":661000,"text":"And to date, there has been a sort of a schizophrenia"},{"time":665000,"text":"in the donor community,"},{"time":667000,"text":"as to how to build basic services"},{"time":670000,"text":"in post-conflict sectors."},{"time":672000,"text":"On the one hand it pays lip service"},{"time":674000,"text":"to the idea of rebuild an effective state"},{"time":678000,"text":"in the image of Scandinavia in the 1950s."},{"time":681000,"text":"Lets develop line ministries of this, that, and the other,"},{"time":684000,"text":"that deliver these services."},{"time":687000,"text":"And it's schizophrenic because in their hearts"},{"time":690000,"text":"donors know that's not a realistic agenda,"},{"time":693000,"text":"and so what they also do is the total bypass:"},{"time":696000,"text":"just fund NGOs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700000,"text":"Neither of those approaches is sensible."},{"time":703000,"text":"And so what I'd suggest"},{"time":707000,"text":"is what I call Independent Service Authorities."},{"time":710000,"text":"It's to split the functions of a monopoly line ministry up into three."},{"time":715000,"text":"The planning function and policy function stays with the ministry;"},{"time":719000,"text":"the delivery of services on the ground,"},{"time":722000,"text":"you should use whatever works --"},{"time":724000,"text":"churches, NGOs, local communities,"},{"time":727000,"text":"whatever works."},{"time":729000,"text":"And in between, there should be a public agency,"},{"time":732000,"text":"the Independent Service Authority,"},{"time":734000,"text":"which channels public money,"},{"time":736000,"text":"and especially donor money,"},{"time":738000,"text":"to the retail providers."},{"time":741000,"text":"So the NGOs become part of a public government system,"},{"time":746000,"text":"rather than independent of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749000,"text":"One advantage of that is that you can allocate money coherently."},{"time":753000,"text":"Another is, you can make NGOs accountable."},{"time":756000,"text":"You can use yardstick competition,"},{"time":758000,"text":"so they have to compete against each other"},{"time":761000,"text":"for the resources."},{"time":763000,"text":"The good NGOs, like Oxfam, are very keen on this idea."},{"time":766000,"text":"They want to have the discipline and accountability."},{"time":772000,"text":"So that's a way to get basic services scaled up."},{"time":775000,"text":"And because the government would be funding it,"},{"time":778000,"text":"it would be co-branding these services."},{"time":780000,"text":"So they wouldn't be provided thanks to"},{"time":784000,"text":"the United States government and some NGO."},{"time":788000,"text":"They would be co-branded"},{"time":790000,"text":"as being done by the post-conflict government, in the country."},{"time":795000,"text":"So, jobs, basic services, finally, clean government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801000,"text":"Clean means follow their money."},{"time":804000,"text":"The typical post-conflict government is so short of money"},{"time":809000,"text":"that it needs our money"},{"time":811000,"text":"just to be on a life-support system."},{"time":814000,"text":"You can't get the basic functions of the state done"},{"time":817000,"text":"unless we put money into the core budget of these countries."},{"time":821000,"text":"But, if we put money into the core budget,"},{"time":825000,"text":"we know that there aren't the budget systems with integrity"},{"time":832000,"text":"that mean that money will be well spent."},{"time":835000,"text":"And if all we do is put money in and close our eyes"},{"time":839000,"text":"it's not just that the money is wasted --"},{"time":841000,"text":"that's the least of the problems --"},{"time":843000,"text":"it's that the money is captured."},{"time":846000,"text":"It's captured by the crooks who are at the heart of the political problem."},{"time":852000,"text":"And so inadvertently we empower the people who are the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":857000,"text":"So building clean government means, yes, provide money"},{"time":860000,"text":"to the budget,"},{"time":862000,"text":"but also provide a lot of scrutiny,"},{"time":867000,"text":"which means a lot of technical assistance that follows the money."},{"time":870000,"text":"Paddy Ashdown, who was the grand high nabob of Bosnia"},{"time":875000,"text":"to the United Nations,"},{"time":877000,"text":"in his book about his experience, he said,"},{"time":879000,"text":"\"I realize what I needed"},{"time":882000,"text":"was accountants without borders,"},{"time":886000,"text":"to follow that money.\""},{"time":888000,"text":"So that's the -- let me wrap up,"},{"time":891000,"text":"this is the package."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894000,"text":"What's the goal?"},{"time":896000,"text":"If we follow this, what would we hope to achieve?"},{"time":900000,"text":"That after 10 years,"},{"time":903000,"text":"the focus on the construction sector"},{"time":906000,"text":"would have produced both jobs"},{"time":908000,"text":"and, hence, security --"},{"time":910000,"text":"because young people would have jobs --"},{"time":912000,"text":"and it would have reconstructed the infrastructure."},{"time":916000,"text":"So that's the focus on the construction sector."},{"time":919000,"text":"The focus on the basic service delivery"},{"time":921000,"text":"through these independent service authorities"},{"time":924000,"text":"would have rescued basic services"},{"time":927000,"text":"from their catastrophic levels,"},{"time":930000,"text":"and it would have given ordinary people"},{"time":933000,"text":"the sense that the government was doing something useful."},{"time":937000,"text":"The emphasis on clean government"},{"time":940000,"text":"would have gradually squeezed out the political crooks,"},{"time":943000,"text":"because there wouldn't be any money"},{"time":947000,"text":"in taking part in the politics."},{"time":949000,"text":"And so gradually the selection,"},{"time":951000,"text":"the composition of politicians,"},{"time":953000,"text":"would shift from the crooked to the honest."},{"time":958000,"text":"Where would that leave us?"},{"time":961000,"text":"Gradually it would shift"},{"time":963000,"text":"from a politics of plunder"},{"time":966000,"text":"to a politics of hope. Thank you."},{"time":969000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}